---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dr. Zahra Salimi | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Profile of Dr. Zahra Salimi, Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise at Brenkley Doctoral College and doctoral supervisor in education leadership and qualitative research.">

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

      <a href="/supervisors" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm mb-8 inline-block">&larr; Back to Supervisors</a>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <div class="card mb-6">
            <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">Dr. Zahra Salimi</h1>
            <p class="text-accent font-medium mb-4">Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise</p>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
              <p><strong class="text-foreground">Specialisms:</strong> Education Leadership, Policy, Practitioner-Researcher Identity</p>
              <p><strong class="text-foreground">Methods:</strong> Qualitative (narrative inquiry, IPA, ethnography)</p>
              <p><strong class="text-foreground">Active researchers:</strong> 4</p>
              <p><strong class="text-foreground">Capacity:</strong> Open to new enquiries</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card mb-6">
            <h2 class="font-bold mb-3">Research Interests</h2>
            <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-2">
              <li>Education leadership and system reform</li>
              <li>Professional identity in educational contexts</li>
              <li>Practitioner-researcher positionality and ethics</li>
              <li>Insider research methodology</li>
              <li>Gender and leadership in education</li>
              <li>Qualitative research design and methods</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2 class="font-bold mb-3">Qualifications</h2>
            <ul class="text-sm text-muted space-y-2">
              <li>PhD in Supply Chain Management, University of Bolton</li>
              <li>MSc in Business Information Systems, University of Bolton</li>
              <li>BSc (Hons) in Business Information Systems, University of Bolton</li>
              <li>Postgraduate Certificate in Teaching and Learning in Higher Education</li>
              <li>Senior Fellow, Higher Education Academy</li>
              <li>Member, UK Academy of Information Systems (UKAIS)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Main content -->
        <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-8">

          <div>
            <p class="section-label mb-3">Biography</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About Dr Salimi</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-muted">
              <p>Dr. Zahra Salimi is the Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise at Brenkley Doctoral College, with responsibility for academic quality assurance across all programmes. She joined Brenkley Doctoral College as a founding member of the academic team, bringing extensive experience in higher and further education leadership and in doctoral supervision.</p>
              <p>Zahra's academic background is in education policy and leadership, with a focus on how educational systems respond to reform agendas and how leaders within those systems navigate the intersection of policy, professional values, and institutional culture. Her own doctoral research examined the experience of women leading post-compulsory education institutions in England, using narrative inquiry to explore identity, legitimacy, and the management of competing expectations.</p>
              <p>As a methodologist, Zahra is a committed advocate for qualitative approaches in practitioner research. She has published on the ethics and epistemology of insider research, the use of interpretive phenomenological analysis in professional doctorate contexts, and the distinctive challenges facing practitioner-researchers who must manage the dual roles of practitioner and researcher within their own organisations.</p>
              <p>In her role as Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise, Zahra oversees admissions, programme design, supervisor development, and assessment processes. She chairs the Quality Assurance Committee and leads Brenkley Doctoral College's annual internal audit processes. She is also the primary contact for researchers who wish to raise concerns about their supervisory experience.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Selected Publications</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="card">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">Salimi, Z. (2024). Navigating dual roles: Practitioner-researchers and the ethics of insider positionality in professional doctorates. <em>International Journal of Research &amp; Method in Education</em>, 47(1), 34–51.</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted">An empirical and theoretical examination of how doctoral researchers who study their own organisations manage the ethical complexity of holding simultaneous insider and researcher identities.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="card">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">Salimi, Z. (2021). Women leading in further education: A narrative inquiry into identity, legitimacy, and resilience. <em>Educational Management Administration &amp; Leadership</em>, 49(4), 580–596.</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted">A narrative inquiry study drawing on in-depth interviews with twelve women in senior leadership roles in English FE colleges.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="card">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground mb-1">Salimi, Z. (2019). Using interpretive phenomenological analysis in professional doctorate research: A methodological guide. <em>Qualitative Research in Education</em>, 8(2), 198–224.</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted">A practical and epistemological guide for practitioner-researchers considering IPA as their primary qualitative methodology.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Current Researchers</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-4 text-sm">Dr. Salimi currently supervises four doctoral researchers. Their work spans education system leadership, policy implementation in multi-academy trusts, the professional identity of newly appointed school leaders, and the experience of international students in UK higher education.</p>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted">Dr. Salimi is currently open to enquiries from new researchers, particularly those working in education, public service, or professional fields where qualitative approaches are appropriate. Please contact us to discuss your research interests.</p>
              <div class="mt-4">
                <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary text-sm">Enquire about supervision</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
